[{"id":"VR834495","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A solid metal sphere has a radius <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"R\"><math alttext=\"R\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>R</mi></math></span></span> and a net charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Q\"><math alttext=\"Q\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>Q</mi></math></span></span>. Which of the following graphs best represents the magnitude <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"E\"><math alttext=\"E\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>E</mi></math></span></span> of the electric field as a function of distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"d\"><math alttext=\"d\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>d</mi></math></span></span> from the center of the sphere?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR834495_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows the graph of two line segments in the first quadrant of a coordinate plane with the origin labeled O. The horizontal axis is labeled d and the value R is indicated just to the right of the origin. The vertical axis is labeled E. The first line segment begins at the origin, slants upward and to the right steeply, and ends above R halfway up the vertical axis. The second line segment begins where the first line segment ends, slants downward and to the right gradually, and ends along the horizontal axis near its end.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR834495.g01.svg\"/></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows the graph of two line segments in the first quadrant of a coordinate plane with the origin labeled O. The horizontal axis is labeled d and the value R is indicated just to the right of the origin. The vertical axis is labeled E. The first line segment begins at the origin, moves horizontally to the right, and ends at R along the horizontal axis. A dashed line is drawn vertically upward from R to a point halfway up the vertical axis. The second line segment begins at the top of this dashed line, slants downward and to the right gradually, and ends along the horizontal axis near its end.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR834495.g02.svg\"/></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows the graph of a line segment and a curve in the first quadrant of a coordinate plane with the origin labeled O. The horizontal axis is labeled d and the value R is indicated just to the right of the origin. The vertical axis is labeled E. The line segment begins at the origin, slants upward and to the right steeply, and ends above R halfway up the vertical axis. The curve begins where the line segment ends, moves downward and to the right rapidly at first and then more gradually, and as it becomes horizontal it ends along the horizontal axis near its end.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR834495.g04.svg\"/></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows the graph of a line segment and a curve in the first quadrant of a coordinate plane with the origin labeled O. The horizontal axis is labeled d and the value R is indicated just to the right of the origin. The vertical axis is labeled E. The line segment begins at the origin, moves horizontally to the right, and ends at R along the horizontal axis. A dashed line is drawn vertically upward from R to a point halfway up the vertical axis. The curve begins at the top of this dashed line, moves downward and to the right rapidly at first and then more gradually, and as it becomes horizontal it ends along the horizontal axis near its end.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR834495.g05.svg\"/></span></p>"],"answer":3}]